@NODE Hardware "Hardware Requirements"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Wherefrom
@NEXT Software


@{JCENTER}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}@{U}HARDWARE REQUIREMENTS@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}



@{JLEFT}You need an Amiga with 512 KByte (better 1 MByte or more), at least OS 2.x and two disk drives or a harddisk.


MultiIndicator was coded on an Amiga 4000-040 with OS 3.0 and tested on:


@{LINDENT 4}    A4000-040 with  18 MByte  OS 3.0 and OS 3.1 and Picasso II@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 4}    A4000-040 with  10 MByte  OS 3.0 and OS 3.1@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 4}    A4000-040 with   6 MByte  OS 3.0 and OS 3.1@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 4}    A4000-030 with  10 MByte  OS 3.0 and OS 3.1@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 4}    A4000-030 with   6 MByte  OS 3.0 and OS 3.1@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 4}    A3000T    with  10 MByte  OS 2.0 and Retina BLT Z3@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 4}    A3000T    with  10 MByte  OS 2.0 and OS 3.1@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 4}    A3000     with  10 MByte  OS 2.0 and OS 3.1 and Retina BLT Z3@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 4}    A3000     with  10 MByte  OS 2.0 and OS 3.1 and OmniBus graphics card@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 4}    A500+     with   1 MByte  OS 2.0@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 4}    A500      with 512 KByte  OS 2.0@{PARD}


@ENDNODE

@NODE Software "Software Requirements"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Hardware
@NEXT Installation


@{JCENTER}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}@{U}SOFTWARE REQUIREMENTS@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}



@{JLEFT}For the installation you need the @{B}Installer@{PLAIN}.


If you want to indicate XPK packed files you need the @{B}XPK-package@{PLAIN}. If you also want to indicate powerpacked files you need also the @{B}PowerPacker.library@{PLAIN}.


If you want to indicate Guide-files you need @{B}AmigaGuide@{PLAIN} or @{B}MultiView@{PLAIN} and the @{B}AmigaGuide.library@{PLAIN}.


All these programs were @{B}not@{PLAIN} included in the MultiIndicator-archive, because you can get the latest versions of these programs from every good mailbox or from PD/FD-disks.


@ENDNODE

@NODE Installation "Installation"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Software
@NEXT Start


@{JCENTER}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}@{U}INSTALLATION@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}



@{JLEFT}Use the @{B}InstallMI_?@{PLAIN}-Script to install MultiIndicator. Or use the respective button if your Installer is in SYS:System/.


@{JCENTER}@{" Danish " SYSTEM "SYS:System/Installer SCRIPT //Install/InstallMI_DK APPNAME MIndicator_V2.3 MINUSER AVERAGE DEFUSER AVERAGE LANGUAGE dansk"}

@{" English " SYSTEM "SYS:System/Installer SCRIPT //Install/InstallMI_GB APPNAME MIndicator_V2.3 MINUSER AVERAGE DEFUSER AVERAGE LANGUAGE english"}

@{" French " SYSTEM "SYS:System/Installer SCRIPT //Install/InstallMI_F APPNAME MIndicator_V2.3 MINUSER AVERAGE DEFUSER AVERAGE LANGUAGE français"}

@{" German " SYSTEM "SYS:System/Installer SCRIPT //Install/InstallMI_D APPNAME MIndicator_V2.3 MINUSER AVERAGE DEFUSER AVERAGE LANGUAGE deutsch"}

@{" Italian " SYSTEM "SYS:System/Installer SCRIPT //Install/InstallMI_I APPNAME MIndicator_V2.3 MINUSER AVERAGE DEFUSER AVERAGE LANGUAGE italiano"}

@{" Spain " SYSTEM "SYS:System/Installer SCRIPT //Install/InstallMI_E APPNAME MIndicator_V2.3 MINUSER AVERAGE DEFUSER AVERAGE LANGUAGE espańol"}

@{" Swedish " SYSTEM "SYS:System/Installer SCRIPT //Install/InstallMI_S APPNAME MIndicator_V2.3 MINUSER AVERAGE DEFUSER AVERAGE LANGUAGE svenska"}


@ENDNODE

@NODE Start "Start MultiIndicator"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Installation
@NEXT Help


@{JCENTER}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}@{U}START MULTIINDICATOR@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}



@{JLEFT}MultiIndicator either can start from the Workbench or from the Shell.



          @{B}Workbench@{PLAIN}


            @{" with Icon " LINK Icon}

            @{" as DefaultTool " LINK DefTool}



          @{" Shell " LINK Shell}


@ENDNODE

@NODE Icon "Start from Workbench with Icon"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Start
@NEXT Help


@{JCENTER}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}@{U}START FROM WORKBENCH WITH ICON@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}


@{JLEFT}For starting MultiIndicator from icon, you have to click on the icon twice. MultiIndicator creates an AppIcon after it was started. If you click this AppIcon twice, an ASL-filerequester appears and you can select the file. If you drag and drop another icon on the AppIcon, than the file or the directory to this icon will be displayed immediately.


    @{U}ToolTypes:@{PLAIN}


@{LINDENT 4}    If you want to change the ToolTypes, click the MultiIndicator icon and select the menuitem Information. Now change the ToolTypes and save it.@{PARD}



@{LINDENT 16}    @{B}Prefsfile@{PLAIN}=<path and name of the @{" preferencefile " LINK Menues}>@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 14}              (MultiIndicator will added the suffix .MIprefs if it wasn't specified and will search in the given path, ENVARC:MIndicator/ and ENV:MIndicator/.)@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 10}    @{B}IconX@{PLAIN}=<X-position of AppIcon>@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 10}    @{B}IconY@{PLAIN}=<Y-position of AppIcon>@{PARD}


@ENDNODE

@NODE DefTool "Start as DefaultTool"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Start
@NEXT Help


@{JCENTER}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}@{U}START AS DEFAULTTOOL@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}



@{JLEFT}If you want to use MultiIndicator as DefaultTool, than the program which should be indicated must have a ProjectIcon. Click this ProjectIcon and select the menuitem Information. The Iconwindow appears including the Default Tool line in which you enter MI with complete path.


If the file Standard.MIprefs exists the fonts, screen, guideindicator and so on were loaded from this file. If Standard.MIprefs doesn't exist, the internal settings were used.


@ENDNODE

@NODE Shell "Start from Shell"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Start
@NEXT Help


@{JCENTER}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}@{U}START FROM SHELL@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}



@{JLEFT}If you start MultiIndicator from the Shell, you can load a @{" preferencefile " LINK Menues}.



@{LINDENT 4}    @{U}Syntax from the Shell:@{PLAIN}@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 7}    MI <@{B}File@{PLAIN} or @{B}Path@{PLAIN}> [@{B}-PREF@{PLAIN} <@{" preferencefile " LINK Menues}>]@{PARD}



@{LINDENT 22}        @{B}File@{PLAIN}          Name of the file to be viewed.@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 22}        @{B}Path@{PLAIN}          Name of the path that should be used for the ASL-filerequester.@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 22}        @{B}-PREF@{PLAIN}         Tells MultiIndicator to load the specified @{" preferencefile " LINK Menues}.@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 22}        @{B}Prefsfile@{PLAIN}     Name and path of the @{" preferencefile " LINK Menues}. (MultiIndicator will add the suffix .MIprefs if it wasn't specified and will be search in the given path, ENVARC:MIndicator/ and ENV:MIndicator/.)@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 22}        @{B}-PUB@{PLAIN}          Tells MultiIndicator to open the window on the named Pubscreen.@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 22}        @{B}Pubscreen@{PLAIN}     Name of the Pubscreen.@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 22}        @{B}?@{PLAIN}             Shows syntax.@{PARD}


@ENDNODE

@NODE Help "Help"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Start
@NEXT Menues


@{JCENTER}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}@{U}HELP@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}



@{JLEFT}Place the pointer about a menuitem or a gadget and press the helpbutton.


The file MI.help must available in the directory ENVARC:MIndicator/ or ENV: MIndicator/. The @{B}InstallMI_?@{PLAIN}-Script or the Guide does this automatically.


@ENDNODE

