@{LINDENT 4}    @{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}ASC@{FG TEXT} & HEX@{PLAIN}            @{B}Miscellaneous@{PLAIN}@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 8}        @{FG HIGHLIGHT}ASC & HEX@{FG TEXT}            @{" Goto... G " LINK Goto}@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 8}        @{FG HIGHLIGHT}ASC@{FG TEXT} & HEX            @{" ASC » HEX " LINK ASC_HEX}@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 8}        @{FG HIGHLIGHT}ASC@{FG TEXT} & HEX            @{" HEX » ASC " LINK HEX_ASC}@{PARD}


@ENDNODE

@NODE Open "Menuitem Open... O"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Menues
@NEXT Gadgets


@{JCENTER}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}@{U}THE MENUITEM OPEN... O@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}



@{JLEFT}Opens an ASL-filerequester in which you can select a new file.


@ENDNODE

@NODE About "Menuitem About... A"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Menues
@NEXT Gadgets


@{JCENTER}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}@{U}THE MENUITEM ABOUT... A@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}



@{JLEFT}Opens a window which shows the name of the program, version and programmer.


@ENDNODE

@NODE Info "Menuitem Info... I"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Menues
@NEXT Gadgets


@{JCENTER}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}@{U}THE MENUITEM INFO... I@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}



@{JLEFT}Opens a window which gives informations about the loaded file, how packer was used (if file compressed with XPK or PowerPacker), the packed length, the unpacked length, the ratio and information about chipmemory and fastmemory.


@ENDNODE

@NODE Quit "Menuitem Quit Q"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Menues
@NEXT Gadgets


@{JCENTER}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}@{U}THE MENUITEM QUIT Q@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}



@{JLEFT}If MultiIndicator was started from Shell or as DefaultTool, than MultiIndicator terminated. If MultiIndicator was started from Workbench, the Quitwindow appears which ask you if you want to only close the MultiIndicatorwindow or if you want to terminate the program.


@ENDNODE

@NODE Load "Menuitem Load..."
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Menues
@NEXT Gadgets


@{JCENTER}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}@{U}THE MENUITEM LOAD...@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}



@{JLEFT}Opens an ASL-filerequester in which you can select and load the preferencefile. The choosen settings will be active immediately.


@ENDNODE

@NODE Save "Menuitem Save"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Menues
@NEXT Gadgets


@{JCENTER}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}@{U}THE MENUITEM SAVE@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}



@{JLEFT}The preferencefile Standard.MIPrefs will be saved in the directories ENVARC:MIndicator/ and ENV:MIndicator/.


@ENDNODE

@NODE Saveas "Menuitem Save as..."
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Menues
@NEXT Gadgets


@{JCENTER}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}@{U}THE MENUITEM SAVE AS...@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}



@{JLEFT}Opens an ASL-filerequester in which you can enter the name of the preferencefile. The suffix .MIprefs will be added if it wasn't entered.


@ENDNODE

@NODE Formfeed "Menuitem FormFeed"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Menues
@NEXT Gadgets


@{JCENTER}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}@{U}THE MENUITEM FORMFEED@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}



@{JLEFT}This menuitem is only available if the selected file is an ASC-file.


Here you can select, if a formfeed is necessary or not.


@ENDNODE

@NODE ESC-Tabs "Menuitem ESC-Tabs"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Menues
@NEXT Gadgets


@{JCENTER}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}@{U}THE MENUITEM ESC-TABS@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}



@{JLEFT}This menuitem is only available if the selected file is an ASC-file.


Here you can select if ESC-sequences and Tabs are shown or not.



@{LINDENT 4}    @{U}ESC-sequences which are rerecognized and executed:@{PLAIN}@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 24}        @{B}ESCc@{PLAIN}            Cleared all modes, but no screenclear@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 24}        @{B}ESC[0m@{PLAIN}          Cleared all modes@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 24}        @{B}ESC[1m@{PLAIN}          Bold on@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 24}        @{B}ESC[3m@{PLAIN}          Italic on@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 24}        @{B}ESC[4m@{PLAIN}          Underline on@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 24}        @{B}ESC[7m@{PLAIN}          Invers on@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 24}        @{B}ESC[8m@{PLAIN}          Backgroundcolor for text@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 24}        @{B}ESC[22m@{PLAIN}         Bold off@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 24}        @{B}ESC[23m@{PLAIN}         Italic off@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 24}        @{B}ESC[24m@{PLAIN}         Underline off@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 24}        @{B}ESC[27m@{PLAIN}         Invers off@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 24}        @{B}ESC[3#m@{PLAIN}         Color (# = 0-7) for text@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 24}        @{B}ESC[39m@{PLAIN}         Color 1 for text@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 24}        @{B}ESC[4#m@{PLAIN}         Text in front of backgroundcolor (# = 0-7)@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 24}        @{B}ESC[49m@{PLAIN}         Text in front of backgroundcolor 0@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 4}    Kombinations of these sequences are recognized. For example: @{B}ESC[1;7;37m@{PLAIN} (bold,invers und textcolor 7).


@{LINDENT 4}    @{U}ESC-sequences which are rerecognized and deleted:@{PLAIN}@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 24}        @{B}ESC[#u@{PLAIN}          Line length #@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 24}        @{B}ESC[#t@{PLAIN}          Line number #@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 24}        @{B}ESC[#x@{PLAIN}          Pixel spacing # from top@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 24}        @{B}ESC[#y@{PLAIN}          Pixel spacing # from left@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 24}        @{B}ESC[xx;yyH@{PLAIN}      Cursor in column xx, line yy@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 24}        @{B}ESC[J@{PLAIN}           Delete at cursor@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 24}        @{B}ESC[@@{PLAIN}           Insert space@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 24}        @{B}ESC[#A@{PLAIN}          Cursor # up@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 24}        @{B}ESC[#B@{PLAIN}          Cursor # down@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 24}        @{B}ESC[#C@{PLAIN}          Cursor # left@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 24}        @{B}ESC[#D@{PLAIN}          Cursor # right@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 24}        @{B}ESC[#E@{PLAIN}          Cursor # lines down@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 24}        @{B}ESC[#F@{PLAIN}          Cursor # lines up@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 24}        @{B}ESC[#K@{PLAIN}          to lineend # delete@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 24}        @{B}ESC[#L@{PLAIN}          # lines insert@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 24}        @{B}ESC[#M@{PLAIN}          # lines delete@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 24}        @{B}ESC[#P@{PLAIN}          # chars delete@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 24}        @{B}ESC[#S@{PLAIN}          scroll up # lines@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 24}        @{B}ESC[#T@{PLAIN}          scroll down # lines@{PARD}


@ENDNODE

@NODE Tabs "Menuitem Tabs"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Menues
@NEXT Gadgets


@{JCENTER}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}@{U}THE MENUITEM TABS@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}



@{JLEFT}This menuitem is only available if the selected file is an ASC-file.


With this menuitem you can choose the tabwidth.


@ENDNODE

@NODE ASC-Line "Menuitem ASC-Line spacing"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Menues
@NEXT Gadgets


@{JCENTER}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}@{U}THE MENUITEM ASC-LINE SPACING@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}



@{JLEFT}This menuitem is only available if the selected file is an ASC-file.


With this menuitem you con choose the ASC-line spacing.


@ENDNODE

@NODE HEX-Line "Menuitem HEX-Line spacing"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Menues
@NEXT Gadgets


@{JCENTER}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}@{U}THE MENUITEM HEX-LINE SPACING@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}



@{JLEFT}This menuitem is only available if the selected file is an HEX-file.


With this menuitem you con choose the HEX-line spacing.


@ENDNODE

@NODE Publicscreen "Menuitem Publicscreen..."
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Menues
@NEXT Gadgets


@{JCENTER}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}@{U}THE MENUITEM PUBLICSCREEN...@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}



@{JLEFT}Shows a list with all opened publicscreens. You can now select the screen, on which the MultiIndicatorwindow will be opened.


@ENDNODE

@NODE Windowsize "Menuitem Windowsize"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Menues
@NEXT Gadgets


@{JCENTER}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}@{U}THE MENUITEM WINDOWSIZE@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}



@{JLEFT}Here you can select if the window use the maximum screensize, the visible screensize or the current windowsize.


@ENDNODE

@NODE Guide "Menuitem Guideindicator..."
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Menues
@NEXT Gadgets


@{JCENTER}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}@{U}THE MENUITEM GUIDEINDICATOR...@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}



@{JLEFT}This menu item is only available if the selected file is an ASC-file.


Opens an ASL-filerequester in which you can select the indicator for the Guide-files.


@ENDNODE

@NODE Editor "Menuitem ASC-Editor..."
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Menues
@NEXT Gadgets


@{JCENTER}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}@{U}THE MENUITEM ASC-EDITOR...@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}



@{JLEFT}This menuitem is only available if the selected file is an ASC-file.


Opens the ASC-editorwindow in which you can change the ASC-editor and the parameters.


@ENDNODE

@NODE HEditor "Menuitem HEX-Editor..."
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Menues
@NEXT Gadgets


@{JCENTER}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}@{U}THE MENUITEM HEX-EDITOR...@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}



@{JLEFT}This menuitem is only available if the selected file is an HEX-file.


Opens the HEX-editorwindow in which you can change the HEX-editor and the parameters.


@ENDNODE

@NODE GadFont "Menuitem Gadgetfont..."
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Menues
@NEXT Gadgets


@{JCENTER}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}@{U}THE MENUITEM GADGETFONT...@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}



@{JLEFT}Opens an ASL-fontrequester in which you can select the font for the gadgets.


@ENDNODE

@NODE ASC-TFont "Menuitem ASC-Textfont..."
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Menues
@NEXT Gadgets


@{JCENTER}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}@{U}THE MENUITEM ASC-TEXTFONT...@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}



@{JLEFT}This menuitem is only available if the selected file is an ASC-file.


Opens an ASL-fontrequester in which you can select the ASC-font for the text. You may not select a proportional font.


@ENDNODE

@NODE HEX-TFont "Menuitem HEX-Textfont..."
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Menues
@NEXT Gadgets


@{JCENTER}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}@{U}THE MENUITEM HEX-TEXTFONT...@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}



@{JLEFT}This menuitem is only available if the selected file is an HEX-file.


Opens an ASL-fontrequester in which you can select the HEX-font for the text. You may not select a proportional font.


@ENDNODE

@NODE Print "Menuitem Print... P"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Menues
@NEXT Gadgets


@{JCENTER}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}@{U}THE MENUITEM PRINT... P@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}



@{JLEFT}This menuitem is only available if the selected file is an ASC-file.


Opens the printer window, in which you can change printer options and start the printaction.



@{LINDET 4}    @{U}Variables for head- and footline:@{PLAIN}


@{LINDET 8}        @{B}#f#@{PLAIN} = filename

@{LINDET 8}        @{B}#d#@{PLAIN} = printdate

@{LINDET 8}        @{B}#t#@{PLAIN} = printtime

@{LINDET 8}        @{B}#p#@{PLAIN} = pagenumber


@ENDNODE

@NODE Clearmarker "MenuitemClear marker C"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Menues
@NEXT Gadgets


@{JCENTER}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}@{U}THE MENUITEM CLEAR MARKER C@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}



@{JLEFT}This menuitem is only available if the selected file is an ASC-file.


With this menuitem you can clear the markers.


@ENDNODE

@NODE Startmarker "Menuitem Startmarker 0"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Menues
@NEXT Gadgets


@{JCENTER}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}@{U}THE MENUITEM STARTMARKER 0@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}



@{JLEFT}This menuitem is only available if the selected file is an ASC-file.


With this menuitem you can set up the startmarker for the areaprintoption (first visible line).


@ENDNODE

@NODE Endmarker "Menuitem Endmarker 1"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Menues
@NEXT Gadgets


@{JCENTER}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}@{U}THE MENUITEM ENDMARKER 1@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}



@{JLEFT}This menuitem is only available if the selected file is an ASC-file.


With this menuitem you can set up the endmarker for the areaprintoption (last visible line).


@ENDNODE

@NODE ASC-Edit "Menuitem ASC-Edit... E"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Menues
@NEXT Gadgets


@{JCENTER}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}@{U}THE MENUITEM ASC-EDIT... E@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}



@{JLEFT}This menuitem is only available if the selected file is an ASC-file.


Starts the choosen ASC-editor with the parameters. The ASC-editor may not detach, then the editing text will be shown.


@{B}Attention !!!@{PLAIN}


If it's a packed file you have to use an ASC-editor which is able to unpack the file before editing it. Otherwise you only get strange characters.


@ENDNODE

@NODE HEX-Edit "Menuitem HEX-Edit... E"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Menues
@NEXT Gadgets


@{JCENTER}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}@{U}THE MENUITEM HEX-EDIT... E@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}



@{JLEFT}This menuitem is only available if the selected file is an HEX-file.


Starts the choosen HEX-editor with the parameters. The HEX-editor may not detach, then the editing text will be shown.


@{B}Attention!!!@{PLAIN}


If it's a packed file you have to use an HEX-editor which is able to unpack the file before editing it.


@ENDNODE

@NODE Goto "Menuitem Goto... G"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Menues
@NEXT Gadgets


@{JCENTER}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}@{U}THE MENUITEM GOTO... G@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}



@{JLEFT}Opens the Goto window in which you can enter the line from where the text would be shown.


@ENDNODE

@NODE ASC_HEX "Menuitem ASC » HEX"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Menues
@NEXT Gadgets


@{JCENTER}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}@{U}THE MENUITEM ASC » HEX@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}



@{JLEFT}This menuitem is only available if the selected file is an ASC-file.


You can switch from the ASC-display to the HEX-display.


@ENDNODE

@NODE HEX_ASC "Menuitem HEX » ASC"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Menues
@NEXT Gadgets


@{JCENTER}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}@{U}THE MENUITEM HEX » ASC@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}


@{JLEFT}This menuitem is only available if the selected file is an ASC-file which you have switched in HEX-mode.


You can switch from the HEX-display to the ASC-display.


@ENDNODE

@NODE Gadgets "Gadgets"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Menues
@NEXT Keyboard


@{JCENTER}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}@{U}GADGETS@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}



@{LINDENT 4}@{JLEFT}    MultiIndicator contains the following gadgets:@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 4}        @{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}ASC & HEX@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}     @{" Textgadget 'Path/Filename' " LINK Text}@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 4}        @{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}ASC & HEX@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}     @{" Buttongadget 'Search' " LINK Search}@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 4}        @{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}ASC & HEX@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}     @{" Buttongadget 'Next' " LINK Next}@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 4}        @{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}ASC & HEX@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}     @{" Buttongadget 'Previous' " LINK Previous}@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 4}        @{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}ASC & HEX@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}     @{" Vertical Propgadget " LINK Vertical}@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 4}        @{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}ASC@{FG TEXT} & HEX@{PLAIN}     @{" Horizontal Propgadget " LINK Horizontal}@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 4}        @{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}ASC & HEX@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}     @{" Closegadget " LINK Close}@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 4}        @{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}ASC & HEX@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}     @{" Zoomgadget " LINK Zoom}@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 4}        @{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}ASC & HEX@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}     @{" Depthgadget " LINK Depth}@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 4}        @{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}ASC & HEX@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}     @{" Sizegadget " LINK Size}@{PARD}


@ENDNODE

@NODE Text "Textgadget 'Path/Filename'"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Gadgets
@NEXT Keyboard


@{JCENTER}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}@{U}THE TEXTGADGET 'PATH/FILENAME'@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}



@{JLEFT}Shows the name of the loaded file. If the name is too long, than the filename will be truncated.


@ENDNODE

@NODE Search "Buttongadget 'Search'"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Gadgets
@NEXT Keyboard


@{JCENTER}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}@{U}THE BUTTONGADGET 'SEARCH'@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}



@{JLEFT}Opens the Searchwindow, in which you can enter the search word and change another options. You can use the @{B}?@{PLAIN} as a pattern.


@ENDNODE

@NODE Next "Buttongadget 'Next'"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Gadgets
@NEXT Keyboard


@{JCENTER}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}@{U}THE BUTTONGADGET 'NEXT'@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}



@{JLEFT}Searches for the next item. If the next item was found, it will be marked. If no item was found, a window appears which informs you.


This gadget is selectable if a searchword is inserted.


@ENDNODE

@NODE Previous "Buttongadget 'Previous'"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Gadgets
@NEXT Keyboard


@{JCENTER}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}@{U}THE BUTTONGADGET 'PREVIOUS'@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}



@{JLEFT}Searches for the previous item. If the previous item was found, it will be marked. If no item was found, a window appears which informs you.


This gadget is selectable if a searchword is inserted.


@ENDNODE

@NODE Vertical "Propgadget vertical"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Gadgets
@NEXT Keyboard


@{JCENTER}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}@{U}THE PROPGADGET VERTICAL@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}



@{JLEFT}With this gadget you can scroll the text by the line (arrows), pages (click below or above the scrollbar) or independent (click on the scrollbar and move).


This works only if the text is longer than one screenpage.


@ENDNODE

@NODE Horizontal "Propgadget horizonal"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Gadgets
@NEXT Keyboard


@{JCENTER}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}@{U}THE PROPGADGET HORIZONTAL@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}



@{JLEFT}This gadget is only available if the selected file is an ASC-file.


With this gadget you can scroll the text by the letter (arrows), pages (click left or right of the scrollbar) or independent (click on the scrollbar and move).


This works only  if the text is wider than one screenpage.


@ENDNODE

@NODE Close "Closegadget"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Gadgets
@NEXT Keyboard


@{JCENTER}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}@{U}THE CLOSEGADGET@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}



@{JLEFT}With gadget has two meanings:


@{LINDENT 3}1. If MultiIndicator was started from Workbench, then only the window will be closed.@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 3}2. If MultiIndicator was started from Shell or as DefaultTool, then the window will be closed an the program terminates.@{PARD}


@ENDNODE

@NODE Zoom "Zoomgadget"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Gadgets
@NEXT Keyboard


@{JCENTER}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}@{U}THE ZOOMGADGET@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}



@{JLEFT}With this gadget you can choose between two windowsizes.


@ENDNODE

@NODE Depth "Depthgadget"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Gadgets
@NEXT Keyboard


@{JCENTER}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}@{U}THE DEPTHGADGET@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}



@{JLEFT}With this gadget you can toggle the window between foreground and background.


@ENDNODE

@NODE Size "Sizegadget"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Gadgets
@NEXT Keyboard


@{JCENTER}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}@{U}THE SIZEGADGET@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}



@{JLEFT}With this gadget you can reduce or enlarge the windowsize.


@ENDNODE

@NODE Keyboard "Keyboard"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Gadgets
@NEXT Mouse


@{JCENTER}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}@{U}KEYBOARD@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}



@{JLEFT}@{B}@{U}Window:@{PLAIN}


@{LINDENT 30}    @{B}ESC:@{PLAIN}                      If an other window as the mainwindow is open, the window will be closed. Is only the mainwindow is open, the mainwindow will be closed and if MultiIndicator was started from Shell or as DefaultTool the program terminates.@{PARD}


@{B}@{U}StringGadgets:@{PLAIN}


@{LINDENT 30}    @{B}Tab:@{PLAIN}                      Next stringgadget activate@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 30}    @{B}Shift + Tab:@{PLAIN}              Previous stringgadget activate@{PARD}


@{B}@{U}Gadgets general:@{PLAIN}


@{LINDENT 30}    @{B}Underlined chars:@{PLAIN}         Activate the button or the stringgadget. (Only if no stringgadget is activated.)@{PARD}


@{B}@{U}Textcontrol:@{PLAIN}


@{LINDENT 30}    @{B}Cursor up:@{PLAIN}                Line up@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 30}    @{B}Cursor down:@{PLAIN}              Line down@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 30}    @{B}Cursor left:@{PLAIN}              char left (only ASC-description)@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 30}    @{B}Cursor right:@{PLAIN}             char right (only ASC-description)@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 30}    @{B}Shift + Cursor...:@{PLAIN}        Page...@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 30}    @{B}Alt + Cursor...:@{PLAIN}          Goto textbegin -end@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 30}    @{B}Ctrl + Cursor...:@{PLAIN}         Goto textbegin -end@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 30}    @{B}Space:@{PLAIN}                    Page down@{PARD}


@{U}Numberblock:@{PLAIN}


@{LINDENT 30}    @{B}5:@{PLAIN}                        See ESC, but only the mainwindow@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 30}    @{B}Cursor up = 8:@{PLAIN}            Line up@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 30}    @{B}Cursor down = 2:@{PLAIN}          Line down@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 30}    @{B}Cursor left = 4:@{PLAIN}          char left (only ASC-description)@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 30}    @{B}Cursor right = 6:@{PLAIN}         char right (only ASC-description)@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 30}    @{B}Pg Up = 9:@{PLAIN}                Page up@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 30}    @{B}Pg Dn = 3:@{PLAIN}                Page down@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 30}    @{B}Home = 7:@{PLAIN}                 Goto textbegin@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 30}    @{B}End = 1:@{PLAIN}                  Goto textend@{PARD}


@ENDNODE

@NODE Mouse "Mouse"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Gadgets
@NEXT ARexx


@{JCENTER}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}@{U}MOUSE@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}



@{JLEFT}When you press and hold the left mousebutton while the pointer is in the textwindow, you can scroll the text.



@{JCENTER}@{B}ASC-mode@{PLAIN}


+-------+-----------------------------------+-------+

|       |                                   |       |

|       |              FAST UP              |       |

|       |                                   |       |

|       +-----------------------------------+   R   |

|   L   |                                   |       |

|       |              SLOW UP              |   I   |

|   E   |                                   |       |

|       +-----------------------------------+   G   |

|   F   |                                   |       |

|       |             SLOW DOWN             |   H   |

|   T   |                                   |       |

|       +-----------------------------------+   T   |

|       |                                   |       |

|       |             FAST DOWN             |       |

|       |                                   |       |

+-------+-----------------------------------+-------+



@{B}HEX-mode@{PLAIN}


+---------------------------------------------------+

|                                                   |

|                      FAST UP                      |

|                                                   |

+---------------------------------------------------+

|                                                   |

|                      SLOW UP                      |

|                                                   |

+---------------------------------------------------+

|                                                   |

|                     SLOW DOWN                     |

|                                                   |

+---------------------------------------------------+

|                                                   |

|                     FAST DOWN                     |

|                                                   |

+---------------------------------------------------+


@ENDNODE

@NODE ARexx "ARexx"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Mouse
@NEXT Language


@{JCENTER}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}@{U}AREXX@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}



@{JLEFT}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}AppIcon:@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}


@{LINDENT 4}    @{B}OPENFROMAPP File/A@{PLAIN}@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 8}        Opens the MultiIndicatorwindow and the file.@{PARD}



@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}Mainwindow:@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}


@{LINDENT 4}    @{B}ACTIVATE ,@{PLAIN}@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 8}        Activates the MutliIndicatorwindow.@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 4}    @{B}ALLTOFRONT ,@{PLAIN}@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 8}        Takes the screen and the MultiIndicatorwindow in front of all other.@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 4}    @{B}GOTOBYTE Byteoffset/A@{PLAIN}@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 8}        The file will be shown at the line in which the Byteoffset is and the first char will be marked.@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 4}    @{B}GOTOLINE Line/A@{PLAIN}@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 8}        The file will be shown at the given line.@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 4}    @{B}HIDETOAPP ,@{PLAIN}@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 8}        Closes the MultiIndicatorwindow. Only the AppIcon were shown. (Only available if MultiIndicator was started about the AppIcon.)@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 4}    @{B}LOAD Prefsfile/A@{PLAIN}@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 8}        Loads the Preferencefile.@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 4}    @{B}OPEN File/A@{PLAIN}@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 8}        Opens the file.@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 4}    @{B}QUIT ,@{PLAIN}@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 8}        Quit MultiIndicator.@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 4}    @{B}SCRTOBACK ,@{PLAIN}@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 8}        Takes the screen in the background.@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 4}    @{B}SCRTOFRONT ,@{PLAIN}@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 8}        Takes the screen in the foreground.@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 4}    @{B}SEARCH Searchword/A@{PLAIN}@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 8}        Serches for the searchword. (Put the $ char in front of the searchword if HEX-search will be useed.)@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 4}    @{B}WINTOBACK ,@{PLAIN}@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 8}        Takes the the MultiIndicatorwindow in the background.@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 4}    @{B}WINTOFRONT ,@{PLAIN}@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 8}        Takes the the MultiIndicatorwindow in the foreground.@{PARD}


@ENDNODE

@NODE Language "Language"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV ARexx
@NEXT History


@{JCENTER}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}@{U}LANGUAGE@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}



@{JLEFT}MultiIndicator supports the languages: English (intern), French (catalog) @{B}Pascal Aubert@{PLAIN}, German (catalog), Italian (catalog) @{B}Marco Mellia@{PLAIN}, Spain (catalog until 1.7) @{B}Jose Garcia@{PLAIN}, Swedish (catalog) @{B}Mikael Silfver@{PLAIN} and @{B}Johan Billing@{PLAIN} and Danish (catalog) @{B}Martin Rix@{PLAIN}.



@{B}@{U}Appeal:@{PLAIN}


I need the @{B}.ct-Files@{PLAIN} for the languages


Norwegian, Dutch, Portuguese and Spanish (>V1.7)


the @{B}.help-Files@{PLAIN} for the languages


French, Italian, Norwegian, Dutch, Portuguese and Spanish,


and the @{B}InstallMI_?@{PLAIN}-Script-Files for the languages


French, Italian, Norwegian, Dutch, Portuguese and Spanish.


For the @{B}.ct-File@{PLAIN} the File MI_?.cd is in the directory Catalogs.


If you make a @{B}.help-File@{PLAIN}, the text mustn't be longer than @{U}16 lines@{PLAIN} and wider than @{U}50 chars@{PLAIN}.



@{B}Thanks in advance@{PLAIN}.


@ENDNODE

@NODE  History "History"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Language
@NEXT Bugs


@{JCENTER}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}@{U}HISTORY@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT}



*************************


@{JLEFT}@{LINDENT 17}03.08.93  @{B}V0.0@{PLAIN}   Programming begins.@{PARD}


@{JCENTER}*************************


@{JLEFT}@{LINDENT 17}12.08.93  @{B}V1.0@{PLAIN}   @{B}First public release.@{PLAIN}@{PARD}


@{JCENTER}*************************


@{JLEFT}@{LINDENT 17}16.08.93  @{B}V1.1@{PLAIN}   New loadroutine for ASC-text       -> considerably faster


New searchroutine for HEX and ASC  -> faster


New viewroutine for ASC-text       -> depends on the new loadroutine@{PARD}


@{JCENTER}*************************


@{JLEFT}@{LINDENT 17}16.08.93  @{B}V1.11@{PLAIN}  Reworked Shell-parameters.@{PARD}


@{JCENTER}*************************


@{JLEFT}@{LINDENT 17}17.08.93  @{B}V1.12@{PLAIN}  ASC-HEX_View can used as DefaultTool.@{PARD}


@{JCENTER}*************************


@{JLEFT}@{LINDENT 17}18.08.93  @{B}V1.2@{PLAIN}   MultiIndicator opens an AppIcon if you start it from Workbench.


Support for ToolTypes.@{PARD}


@{JCENTER}*************************


@{JLEFT}@{LINDENT 17}18.08.93  @{B}V1.21@{PLAIN}  Now you can select in the Searchwindow if the search should always start from the beginning and if the capitalization should be taken into account.@{PARD}


@{JCENTER}*************************


@{JLEFT}@{LINDENT 17}18.08.93  @{B}V1.22@{PLAIN}  Now with textcontrol from the keyboard.@{PARD}


@{JCENTER}*************************


@{JLEFT}@{LINDENT 17}19.08.93  @{B}V1.23@{PLAIN}  Name of the program is now MultiIndicator.


Keyboardcontrol like CygnusEd implemented. (Boris Jakubaschk)@{PARD}


@{JCENTER}*************************


@{JLEFT}@{LINDENT 17}                 @{B}Second public release.@{PLAIN}@{PARD}


@{JCENTER}*************************


@{JLEFT}@{LINDENT 17}21.08.93  @{B}V1.3@{PLAIN}   MultiIndicator can indicate ESC-sequences and Tabs.@{PARD}


@{JCENTER}*************************


@{JLEFT}@{LINDENT 17}25.08.93  @{B}V1.4@{PLAIN}   XPK-Packer and PowerPacker support.


Infowindow available.


Buttongadgets change the look if you selct them. (Boris Jakubaschk)


Keyboardcontrol changed. Alt -> Ctrl. (Boris Jakubaschk)@{PARD}


@{JCENTER}*************************


@{JLEFT}@{LINDENT 17}30.08.93  @{B}V1.5@{PLAIN}   Print option for ASC-Texts implement.@{PARD}


@{JCENTER}*************************


@{JLEFT}@{LINDENT 17}                 @{B}Third public release.@{PLAIN}@{PARD}


@{JCENTER}*************************


@{JLEFT}@{LINDENT 17}02.09.93  @{B}V1.5a@{PLAIN}  Spanish Catalog from @{B}José Garcia@{PLAIN}.


Catalogs now work under OS3.x.


Small bugs removed.@{PARD}


@{JCENTER}*************************


@{JLEFT}@{LINDENT 17}09.10.93  @{B}V1.6@{PLAIN}   NewLookMenues under OS3.x.


In gadgets you can use proportional fonts.


Window get a zoom gadget.


Print window reworked.


Variables in head- footline allowed.


The meaning of formfeed has changed!


Checkboxes and MXbuttons scaleable under OS3.x.


Graphicsbug in the pubscreenwindow under OS3.x removed.


Searchword will be indicated if it wasn't found.


One enforcerhit removed.


Text without end of line in the last line view exactely.


More than one packstep allowed.


Program can be terminated with ESC-button.


Waitpointer changed -> faster


If you start the program from the AppIcon, it remembers the last path.


Help implemented.


Dynamic stack implemented. No stack is necessary, but no control with mungwall possible.


Installer script added.


AmigaGuide manual added.


Swedish Catalog from @{B}Mikael Silfver@{PLAIN}.


New menuitem Open available. (Mikael Silfver)


Only the visible area of the screen used. (Jens Bönisch)


MI always remembers the last path.


@{U}For keyboardfetishists !@{PLAIN}


Windows (except password window and ASL-requester) can be closed with ESC.


In the searchwindow you have to press return twice if the stringgadget is activated and you want to start the search.@{PARD}


@{JCENTER}*************************


@{JLEFT}@{LINDENT 17}                 @{B}Fourth public release.@{PLAIN}@{PARD}


@{JCENTER}*************************


@{JLEFT}@{LINDENT 17}16.11.93  @{B}V1.7@{PLAIN}   Text in the password window is invisible.


In stringgadgets you can jump with cursor up and cursor down.


Program optimized -> about 22% shorter.


A few internal improvements.


Now accessible via @{" E-Mail " LINK Author}.


Swedish Help-File from @{B}Mikael Silfver@{PLAIN}.


You can now use the Alt key instead of the Ctrl key. (Mikael Silfver)


Publicscreen can now be select with a doubleclick. (Mikael Silfver)


Small bugs removed. (Mikael Silfver)


MI now knows Hex-Code 9b resp. ASC-code 155. This is the same as 'ESC['. (Is used in many BBSs)@{PARD}


@{JCENTER}*************************


@{JLEFT}@{LINDENT 17}                 @{B}Fifth public release.@{PLAIN}@{PARD}


@{JCENTER}*************************


@{JLEFT}@{LINDENT 17}12.01.94  @{B}V1.7@{PLAIN}   French Catalog from @{B}Pascal Aubert@{PLAIN}.


If the xpk????.librarys are be installed, the version will be checked. (Not all !!! Sorry)@{PARD}


@{JCENTER}*************************


@{JLEFT}@{LINDENT 17}                 @{B}Sixth public release.@{PLAIN}@{PARD}


@{JCENTER}*************************


@{JLEFT}@{LINDENT 17}24.02.94  @{B}V1.8@{PLAIN}   You can switch an ASC-text from ASC-mode to HEX-mode and back from HEX-mode to ASC-mode. (Michael Arlt)


You can set an ASC-textfont and a HEX-textfont. (Mikael Silfver)


You can call an external editor if the text is a ASC-text.


You can scroll the text if you press and hold the left mousebutton while the pointer is in the text-window.


You can choose the tabwidth. (Mikael Silfver)


You can save settings with @{B}Save@{PLAIN} and @{B}Save as@{PLAIN} and load settings with @{B}Load@{PLAIN}.


Only one Shell-argument and three ToolTypes are available.


Shell: With -PREF <@{" preferencefile " LINK Menues}> you can load the settings you wish.


ToolTypes: Prefsfile=<@{" preferencefile " LINK Menues}> same as Shell.


You can hand over printersettings without printing.


Formfeeds in the text will be removed.


In the Shell you can hand over a filename or pathname.


If you drop a drawer- or a diskicon on the MultiIndicatorappicon the ASL-filerequester take with path.


If you start MultiIndicator from the AppIcon then you can quit the program only if you choose the menuitem @{B}Quit@{PLAIN}.


Two enforcerhits removed.


Publicscreen @{B}Default@{PLAIN} added. So I hope the problems with publicscreenmanagers are solved. @{B}Default@{PLAIN} means that the MultiIndicatorwindow will be opend on the defaultpublicscreen. (Adrian Demarais)


Installer, AmigaGuide, XPK and the PowerPacker.library are removed, because the archive was too large.


Memory will be allocated with MEMF_ANY, so you can use virtual memory.


Reworked english Help-File. (Johan Billing)@{PARD}


@{JCENTER}*************************


@{JLEFT}@{LINDENT 17}                 @{B}Seventh public release.@{PLAIN}@{PARD}


@{JCENTER}*************************


@{JLEFT}@{LINDENT 17}20.03.94  @{B}V1.8@{PLAIN}   Swedish Catalog and swedish Help-File become complete. (Johan Billing)@{PARD}


@{JCENTER}*************************


@{JLEFT}@{LINDENT 17}                 @{B}AmiNET public release.@{PLAIN}@{PARD}


@{JCENTER}*************************


@{JLEFT}@{LINDENT 17}22.03.94  @{B}V1.8@{PLAIN}   Reworked english Document. (Johan Billing)@{PARD}


@{JCENTER}*************************


@{JLEFT}@{LINDENT 17}23.03.94  @{B}V1.81@{PLAIN}  If you start MultiIndicator from Shell and no filename or directory will be hand over, then MultiIndicator use the latest Shellpath. (Johan Billing)


When lines in ASC-texts ends with CR+LF or LF+CR, then MultiIndicator replaces the CR+LF or LF+CR with CR. (Johan Billing)


A "Sizegadget" at the bottom right corner implemented. This Sizegadget isn't a normal Sizegadget, because you can only choose, if you use full- or halfscreen. Is with enough ? (Bill Bennett)


Searchroutine improved -> up to 20% faster.@{PARD}


@{JCENTER}*************************


@{JLEFT}@{LINDENT 17}03.04.94  @{B}V1.82@{PLAIN}  The spacing between the lines in ASC- and HEX-mode can now be changed.


Publicscreenbug removed.


Zoomgadgetbug removed.@{PARD}


@{JCENTER}*************************


@{JLEFT}@{LINDENT 17}                 @{B}Eighth public release.@{PLAIN}@{PARD}


@{JCENTER}*************************


@{JLEFT}@{LINDENT 17}03.05.94  @{B}V1.85@{PLAIN}  A little ARexxPort implemented.


Texts with more than 100 ESC-sequences in one line were shown correctly.


Current line and whole lines were shown.


New menuitem @{B}Goto@{PLAIN} implemented.


Italian Catalog from @{B}Marco Mellia@{PLAIN}.@{PARD}


@{JCENTER}*************************


@{JLEFT}@{LINDENT 17}                 @{B}Ninth public release.@{PLAIN}@{PARD}


@{JCENTER}*************************


@{JLEFT}@{LINDENT 17}20.07.94  @{B}V1.9@{PLAIN}   You can call an external HEX-editor.


New ARexx-command GOTOBYTE.


Searchpattern @{B}?@{PLAIN} implemented.


ALLTOBACK will be replaced by SCRTOBACK and WINTOBACK.


Page down with the space key. (Marco Mellia)@{PARD}


@{JCENTER}*************************


@{JLEFT}@{LINDENT 17}                 @{B}Tenth public release.@{PLAIN}@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 17}                 @{B}AmiNET public release.@{PLAIN}@{PARD}


@{JCENTER}*************************


@{JLEFT}@{LINDENT 17}28.08.94  @{B}V2.0@{PLAIN}   You can now scroll left and right with the mouse.


If you would search for @{B}$@{PLAIN} in the HEX-mode, you have to enter @{B}$$@{PLAIN}.


The window ist full resizeable. (Bill Bennett and Michael Arlt)


You can select an area to print.


3 windowsizes are available: maximum screensize, visible screenarea and current windowsize. (Michael Arlt)


Das MultiIndicatorwindow is now an AppWindow. (Michael Arlt)


MultiIndicator is SysIHack-compatibel :-)


2 new ARexx-commands SCRTOFRONT und WINTOFRONT.


ARexx-command GOTOBYTE have chanced a little.


Guides rewrite.


Docs included.


An additional MultiIndicatorversion without dynamic stack included. So you can test MultiIndicator with MungWall.

@{B}Attention:@{PLAIN} This Version needs a stack of 8192 Bytes !


@{FG FILL}@{B}New E-Mail-Address !!!@{PLAIN}@{FG TEXT} (fatso@turtle.insider.sub.de)@{PARD}


@{JCENTER}*************************


@{JLEFT}@{LINDENT 17}                 @{B}Eleventh public release.@{PLAIN}@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 17}                 @{B}AmiNET public release.@{PLAIN}@{PARD}


@{JCENTER}*************************


@{JLEFT}@{LINDENT 17}11.09.94  @{B}V2.1@{PLAIN}   MultiIndicator can quit with the 5-key from the numberblock.


No Problems with more MultiIndicators and packed Guides.@{PARD}


@{JCENTER}*************************


@{JLEFT}@{LINDENT 17}                 @{B}Twelfth public release.@{PLAIN}@{PARD}


@{JCENTER}*************************


@{JLEFT}@{LINDENT 17}26.09.94  @{B}V2.2@{PLAIN}   ASC-chars < 32 in Guide-files allowed. (Bruno Jansen)


After loading a file the AppIcon disappears and it appears only the file was closed. (Bruno Jansen)@{PARD}


@{JCENTER}*************************


@{JLEFT}@{LINDENT 17}                 @{B}Thirteenth public release.@{PLAIN}@{PARD}


@{JCENTER}*************************


@{JLEFT}@{LINDENT 17}13.11.94  @{B}V2.3@{PLAIN}   -PUB Keyword implemented again. (Bernd Grunwald)


Danish Catalog, Help-File and Installscript from Martin Rix.@{PARD}


@{JCENTER}*************************


@{JLEFT}@{LINDENT 17}                 @{B}Fourteenth public release.@{PLAIN}@{PARD}


@{JCENTER}*************************


